.TH "batadv_tp_wait_available" 9 "batadv_tp_wait_available" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_tp_wait_available \- wait until congestion window becomes free or timeout is reached
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" batadv_tp_wait_available
.BI "(struct batadv_tp_vars *tp_vars "  ","
.BI "size_t plen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tp_vars" 12
the private data of the current TP meter session
.IP "plen" 12
size of the payload of a single message
.SH "RETURN"
0 if the condition evaluated to false after the timeout elapsed,
1 if the condition evaluated to true after the timeout elapsed, the
remaining jiffies (at least 1) if the condition evaluated to true before
the timeout elapsed, or -ERESTARTSYS if it was interrupted by a signal.
